\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 In the last video, we gave the basic idea of how to construct a bootstrap confidence interval to capture the true value. We have an estimate calculated from our data. It might be a mean, a median, a percentage, or something else, but we know it's not going to be quite right. We calculate the same quantity for a large number of bootstrap resamples (from the data) and take the minimum to the maximum of what we've seen as the interval of values we think will probably cover the truth. That's it except for one small detail. (We trim up the extreme biggest and smallest values before reading off the interval.) Well that's the recipe, but does it work?\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260\sa326\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/data-to-insight/8/steps/508396#"}}{\fldrslt 
